FBIS4-41857 "drsov125_b_94021" FBIS-SOV-94-125 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Gerashchenko Advocates Protectionism for Banks Gerashchenko Advocates Protectionism for Banks LD2806153394 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service in English 1100 GMT 28 Jun 94 LD2806153394 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service English BFN [Text] Only the foreign banks that can boast a first-rate reputation and are regarded as reliable partners should be attracted to Russia. This has been stated by the chairman of Russia's Central Bank, Viktor Gerashchenko. Speaking in Moscow at a conference of the Consultative Council for Foreign Investment, he emphasized the necessity to preserve protectionism in respect of home banks. Mr. Gerashchenko also said that in 1993 Russia's gold and hard currency reserves had tripled. By the first of this month they amounted to $5.6 billion.
